===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''mos''; akin to Anglo-Saxon. ''meós'', German ''moos'', Old High German ''mos'', ''mios'', Icelandic ''mosi'', Danish ''mos'', Swedish ''mossa'', Latin ''muscus''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-moss.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒs|-ɒs]]

===Noun===
'''moss'''
# Any of various small green [[plant]]s of the [[class]] ''[[Musci]]'' of the [[division]] ''[[Bryophyta]]''
# A [[patch]] of [[ground]] covered with such plants
# Any of various other non-related plants of a similar appearance

